<paragraph blockId="41.[812,1457,1915,2019]" lastBlockId="42.[131,778,215,345]" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="799" pageId="41" pageNumber="798">
REMARQUES TAXONOMIQUES. — Représentant local du groupe de 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker, 1855" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1855" box="[814,1100,1941,1965]" class="Insecta" family="Saturniidae" genus="Copaxa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="798" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="canella">
<emphasis box="[814,958,1941,1965]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="798">Copaxa canella</emphasis>
Walker, 1855
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[1116,1164,1942,1965]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="798">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="LEMAIRE C." box="[1172,1311,1941,1966]" pageId="41" pageNumber="798" refId="ref50152" refString="LEMAIRE C. 1978. - Les Attacidae americains. The Attacidae of America. Claude Lemaire (Ed.), Neuilly-sur-Seine 1. Attacinae. 238 p." type="book" year="1978">Lemaire 1978</bibRefCitation>
). Les données génétiques attestent que 
<taxonomicName authority="Maassen &amp; Weymer, 1881" authorityName="Maassen &amp; Weymer" authorityYear="1881" box="[1053,1457,1968,1992]" class="Insecta" family="Saturniidae" genus="Copaxa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="798" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simson">
<emphasis box="[1053,1193,1968,1992]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="798">Copaxa simson</emphasis>
Maassen &amp; Weymer, 1881
</taxonomicName>
et 
<taxonomicName authority="Beneluz, 2008" authorityName="Beneluz" authorityYear="2008" box="[835,1104,1994,2019]" class="Insecta" family="Saturniidae" genus="Copaxa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="798" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bireni">
<emphasis box="[835,963,1994,2018]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="798">Copaxa bireni</emphasis>
Bénéluz, 2008
</taxonomicName>
représentent la même espèce. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maassen &amp; Weymer" authorityYear="1881" class="Insecta" family="Saturniidae" genus="Copaxa" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="799" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="798" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simson">
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="799" pageId="41" pageNumber="798">Copaxa simson</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
est également connu de quelques stations du 
<collectingCountry box="[660,771,215,239]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="42" pageNumber="799">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[134,212,241,265]" name="Panama" pageId="42" pageNumber="799">Panamá</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[220,318,241,265]" name="Venezuela" pageId="42" pageNumber="799">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[326,425,241,265]" name="Colombia" pageId="42" pageNumber="799">Colombie</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[433,521,243,269]" name="Ecuador" pageId="42" pageNumber="799">Équateur</collectingCountry>
occidental, 
<collectingCountry box="[635,690,241,265]" name="Peru" pageId="42" pageNumber="799">Pérou</collectingCountry>
et 
<collectingCountry box="[717,774,241,265]" name="Brazil" pageId="42" pageNumber="799">Brésil</collectingCountry>
. Le nouveau statut de 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beneluz" authorityYear="2008" box="[330,462,268,292]" class="Insecta" family="Saturniidae" genus="Copaxa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="799" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bireni">
<emphasis box="[330,462,268,292]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="799">Copaxa bireni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
est justifié par les caractéristiques morphologiques de la population guyanaise (coloration brune du mâle et taille réduite des individus des deux sexes).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
